               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360509-name-995" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-995" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-995" type="surname" value="KENT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-995" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE KENT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. On the 29th of April I was on duty at Mr. Crosby's, a carpenter, in Kingsland-road—I watched the two prisoner for an hour, loitering about the shop of Mr. Crosby, talking to each other, backwards and forwards—I saw Ball stand on one side the shop, and the other on the other side—I saw Ball take the chair from the shop and walk away with it—I took him into custody—the other walked off—he was close to Ball when he took the property—I secured them both—this is the chair.</p>
